ast.name: RPN Calculator
ast.comment: A HP-like pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-10-18: ROUND now rounds to display settings, as stated in online help (always rounded to whole numbers previously). Fixed y^ calculation for y=ax+bxÂ³ correlation function. Additional quadratic trigonometric correlation function (13 in total now). Plus some minor refinements.

body.text: Visual feedback for the pressed key:

2: transform (a',b') to (a,b) after calculating the linear regression
